    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere are methods `nvim_get_mark()`, `nvim_buf_get_mark()`, `nvim_del_mark()`, `nvim_buf_del_mark()`, however, there is only 'nvim_buf_set_mark()`. I cant find a way to use the latter to set global marks, as on first load of Neovim I wouldnt have any buffers.\r\n\r\nThe use case is being able to automatically set marks in some situations based on filename. Specifically, I am storing global marks from `nvim_get_mark()` when switching git worktrees, then trying to set them again when switching back.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAdd API method `nvim_set_mark()` similar to the other global mark method that can set global marks with maybe buffername or absolute path? I guess it would be similar to how neovim restores global marks from the shada file.",
